@BenjaminR That's true but all furniture is still developed toward a human average. You make a chair to fit the largest portion of the population as possible.

There are standard heights for chairs and tables as well as desks and stools.

If a person is asking for themselves or a specific individual, that's a completely different question than this general one.

@FreeMan I cut hardboard into strips. I aligned strips on either side of the pegs and marked the width. Then I used  a chisel to notch out a half-square. I did the same thing on the other side and glued the panels together. Repeated for the other pair of pegs. Cut another panel to fill the remaining space. Then I trimmed the sides with a circular saw.

Unfortunately when i took it to the glass cutter they said it was too big to do with regular glass so they could only use tempered with circular holes XD

If I did it again, I would have made the template beforehand and put pegs in after.
